<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4679> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4679" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "3 The date of the praetorships of Iunius and Publicius, and the curule aedileships of Flaminius and Plaetorius must be later than the term of the Censors elected about July 70 (Cic. Cluent. 126) and precede Cicero's praetorship in 66 (147). As Flaminius and Plaetorius were then in charge of the Quaestio de sicariis it is probable that, like Caesar in 64, they held the office of Iudex Quaestionis in the year following their aedileship. Accordingly, I place their aedileship and the praetorship of lunius and Publicius in 67 (see Wehrmann, FP 48, note; and Münzer, RE, Flaminius no. 4). Sydenham (lxiv) dates Plaetorius in 68." .
